For each dataset, two types of properties are considered: node properties and link properties.  The node properties are defined by the relative number of nodes possessing a certain attribute (gender or presence of keyword "IS"), while the link properties are defined by the ratio of edges connecting nodes with that specific attribute. This table provides a summary of the sensitive properties considered in the experiment.
